<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="174" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1081,1504]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,269,1081,1107]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Remarks:</emphasis>
The relationship between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baird" authorityYear="1845" box="[580,704,1081,1107]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cyprididae</taxonomicName>
representatives of the genera 
<emphasis box="[1057,1160,1081,1107]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Harbinia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tsao, L. P." box="[1170,1296,1081,1108]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" pagination="48 - 49" refId="ref6584" refString="Tsao, L. P. (1959) Harbinia Tsao, 1959. In: Nechayeva, M. A., Liu, Z. Y., SU, D. Y., Shou, Z. X., Tian, K. Z. &amp; Tsao, L. P. (Eds.), Ostracodes of Lower Chalk Deposit of Valley Sunlyao. Geology Press, Beijing, pp. 48 - 49." type="book chapter" year="1959">Tsao, 1959</bibRefCitation>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bate, 1972" authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1972" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Pattersoncypris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bate, R. H." box="[267,390,1117,1144]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" pagination="379 - 393" refId="ref3876" refString="Bate, R. H. (1972) Phosphatized Ostracods with Appendages from the Lower Cretaceous of Brazil. Paleontology, 15, 379 - 393." type="journal article" year="1972">Bate, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has been debated since 
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A." box="[668,874,1117,1144]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" refId="ref4252" refString="Do Carmo, D. A. (1998) Taxonomia, paleoecologia e distribuicao estratigrafica dos ostracodes da Formacao Alagamar (Cretaceo Inferior), bacia Potiguar, Brasil. PhD Thesis. Universidade Federal do Rio Grande do Sul, Porto Alegre, 156 pp." type="book" year="1998">Do Carmo (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Whatley, R. &amp; Queiroz Neto, J. V. Q. &amp; Coimbra, J. C." box="[885,1154,1117,1144]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" pagination="790 - 799" refId="ref4557" refString="Do Carmo, D. A., Whatley, R., Queiroz Neto, J. V. Q. &amp; Coimbra, J. C. (2008) On the validity of two Lower Cretaceous non-ma- rine ostracode genera: biostratigraphic and paleogeographic implications. Journal of Paleontology, 82, 790 - 799. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 07 - 008.1" type="journal article" year="2008">
Do Carmo 
<emphasis box="[1013,1071,1117,1143]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">et al.</emphasis>
(2008)
</bibRefCitation>
discusses the taxonomic aspects involving 
<emphasis box="[354,457,1153,1179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Harbinia</emphasis>
, formalizing 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1972" box="[610,787,1154,1179]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[610,787,1154,1179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Pattersoncypris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as its junior synonym and reallocating four subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="Krommelbein &amp; Weber, 1971" authorityName="Krommelbein &amp; Weber" authorityYear="1971" box="[151,701,1189,1215]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Hourcqia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulata">
<emphasis box="[151,364,1189,1215]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Hourcqia angulata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Krommelbein, K. &amp; Weber, R." box="[370,701,1189,1215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" pagination="1 - 93" refId="ref5038" refString="Krommelbein, K. &amp; Weber, R. (1971) Ostracoden des &quot; Nordost-Brasilianischen Wealden &quot;. Geologisches Jahrbuch, 115, 1 - 93." type="journal article" year="1971">
Krömmelbein &amp; Weber, 
<quantity box="[645,701,1189,1215]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.00634" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" unit="in" value="1971.0">1971</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<emphasis box="[849,952,1189,1215]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Harbinia</emphasis>
. Both proposals were refused subsequently by 
<bibRefCitation author="Poropat, S. F. &amp; Colin, J. P." box="[185,459,1225,1252]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" pagination="699 - 719" refId="ref5511" refString="Poropat, S. F. &amp; Colin, J. P. (2012 b) Reassessment of the Early Cretaceous non-marine ostracod genera Hourcqia Krommelbein, 1965 and Pattersoncypris Bate, 1972 with the description of a new genus, Kroemmelbeincypris. Journal of Paleontology, 86, 699 - 719. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 11 - 140 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2012">Poropat &amp; Colin (2012b)</bibRefCitation>
who reviewed these taxa and suggested the revalidation of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1972" box="[1106,1279,1226,1251]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1106,1279,1226,1251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Pattersoncypris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Krommelbein, 1965" authorityName="Krommelbein" authorityYear="1965" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Hourcqia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1332,1436,1226,1251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Hourcqia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Krommelbein, K." box="[151,379,1261,1288]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" pagination="59 - 74" refId="ref4951" refString="Krommelbein, K. (1965) Ostracoden aus der nicht-marinen Unter-Kreide (&quot; Westafrikanischer Wealden &quot;) des Congo-Kustenbeckens. Meyniana, 15, 59 - 74." type="journal article" year="1965">Krömmelbein, 1965</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, describing also the new genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Poropat &amp; Colin, 2012" authorityName="Poropat &amp; Colin" authorityYear="2012" box="[732,1230,1261,1288]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Kroemmelbeincypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[732,964,1261,1287]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Kroemmelbeincypris</emphasis>
Poropat &amp; Colin, 2012
</taxonomicName>
. This proposal has also received criticism, 
<bibRefCitation author="Do Carmo, D. A. &amp; Coimbra, J. C. &amp; Whatley, R. C. &amp; Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Citon, R. T. P." box="[424,695,1297,1324]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" pagination="91 - 104" refId="ref4300" refString="Do Carmo, D. A., Coimbra, J. C., Whatley, R. C., Antonietto, L. S. &amp; Citon, R. T. P. (2013) Taxonomy of limnic Ostracoda (Crustacea) from the Alagamar Formation, middle-upper Aptian, Potiguar Basin, Northeastern Brazil. Journal of Paleontology, 87, 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 11 - 108 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Do Carmo 
<emphasis box="[553,604,1297,1323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">et al</emphasis>
. (2013)
</bibRefCitation>
argued that features considered by 
<bibRefCitation author="Poropat, S. F. &amp; Colin, J. P." box="[1105,1393,1297,1324]" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" pagination="699 - 719" refId="ref5511" refString="Poropat, S. F. &amp; Colin, J. P. (2012 b) Reassessment of the Early Cretaceous non-marine ostracod genera Hourcqia Krommelbein, 1965 and Pattersoncypris Bate, 1972 with the description of a new genus, Kroemmelbeincypris. Journal of Paleontology, 86, 699 - 719. https: // doi. org / 10.1666 / 11 - 140 R. 1" type="journal article" year="2012">Poropat &amp; Colin (2012b)</bibRefCitation>
are shared with the 
<emphasis box="[330,433,1333,1359]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Harbinia</emphasis>
genus, further pointing out that one of the distinctive characters for the description of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poropat &amp; Colin" authorityYear="2012" box="[151,383,1369,1395]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Kroemmelbeincypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,383,1369,1395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Kroemmelbeincypris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
causes dichotomy within the clade itself, since the anteroventral inclined posterior end, which separates them from 
<emphasis box="[384,487,1405,1431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Harbinia</emphasis>
, is not present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Poropat &amp; Colin, 2012" authorityName="Poropat &amp; Colin" authorityYear="2012" box="[685,1111,1405,1432]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Kroemmelbeincypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="symmetrica">
<emphasis box="[685,846,1406,1431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">K. symmetrica</emphasis>
Poropat &amp; Colin, 2012
</taxonomicName>
. In view of the actual knowledge concerning the taxonomy of the genera discussed above, the authors have chosen to allocate the new species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bate" authorityYear="1972" box="[180,357,1478,1503]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Pattersoncypris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="3" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[180,357,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="174">Pattersoncypris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for now.
</paragraph>
